wikipedia_page.main: Selby Attree Horne Ash (1836 – 8 September 1870) was an English cricketer. He played one first-class match for Cambridge University Cricket Club in 1858.Ash was educated at Tonbridge School and Jesus College, Cambridge. He graduated from Cambridge University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1859, and was curate of Hadleigh, Suffolk from 1861 to 1863.
